[When I read in some accounts of the medical responders contacting the victims and having itching, reddening skin and eyes, and tearing, I thought one of the several known nerve agents may be involved. Most of the nerve agents block acetylcholinesterase of the nerves causing them to continue to fire. Atropine is one treatment. There will surely be more about this in the coming days.

VX is a nerve agent and was involved in the killing of the half-brother of North Korea's leader Kim Jong-un in 2017. It is a very rapid acting agent and the victim was unable to be treated in a timely fashion and died.

Hopefully these current victims are getting appropriate treatment and will recover. - Mod.TG

